Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from contrast enhanced box in Page 03
And	I go to Page 06 of Hip MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Synovia, mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' radio button

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Haemarthrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Loose body' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bony erosions (synovial insertion)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Perifocal soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Periarticular calcification' checkbox is enabled

And 'No' radio button is enabled
And 'Low' radio button is enabled
And 'Pronounced' radio button is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu is enabled
And '> 1 lesion, same entity' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Loose body' checkbox
Then '> 1 lesion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Max. diameter' input field is enabled

When I select 'Low' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Marginal' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Pronounced' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Marginal' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled

When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 1' dropdown menu
Then 'Suspected' checkbox is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis 2' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinated' checkbox is enabled
